data.title: Great Place For Family Pizza Nights or Sports Events
data.text: Features and awesome projection screen for sports viewing along with other T.V.s on site and the buffet is awesome. Pizzas are full and flavorful and the kids will enjoy the video area. A little smaller than the average pizza place but makes for a more cozy gathering.

data.title: Just ok
data.text: The breadsticks were ok but the sauce was cold and had too much basil.  Breadsticks were more like bread, could've used butter. Very average pizza. Place is worn and old looking. Service was friendly and quick. Wouldn't return.

data.title: Quality without compromise is the so important to the owner
data.text: This past weekend, my wife's family was having a reunion and so the idea of having a potluck just wasn't what everyone wanted.  So, it was decided that pizza would be ideal.  Choices abound with your typical large company brands, but they just didn't have the hometown feeling.  We choose V.I.P. Pizza to cater the get together.  In speaking with the owner, she told us she uses only fresh ingredients, such sliced linguicia instead of your usual crumbles.  If you're into good quality foods that means the difference of food which is pleasing to the palate.  The choices of toppings were very impressive.  I totally recognize Tulare is not a hub of entertainment. However, if you're traveling on Highway 99 and you're in the mood for pizza which will not disappoint you, then you must not pass up the opportunity to try V.I.P.'s offerings.

data.title: We did take out...it was tasty!
data.text: Ordered at the restaurant on K Street. Went to get gas while pizza cooked.  Came back to find that the sausage pizza I ordered, was cooked as pepperoni.  The staff was very apologetic.  Bought me a beer while I waited. Restaurant was very busy as every little league team in Tulare must have been there.  They took very good care of me while I waited, despite a packed restaurant.  Very great staff.  Would definitely recommend.  The sausage pizza was delicious and cut into small slices.  Perfect for our group!

data.title: Best Local Pizza!
data.text: Very popular local Pizza joint. Family Friendly with big screen TV's and games for the kids. Good Pizza and sandwiches. Nice salad bar. Lots of beer on tap.

data.title: If you are in the mood for affordable pizza lunch buffet, this is the place!
data.text:
Once in awhile, I travel through Tulare and stop by V.I.P. Pizza.

A great place to watch sports games and eat pizza, but most of all, coming by and taking advantage of the lunch buffet.

It's important to note that this is not like Round Table lunch buffet, with several pizzas all ready to go.  Also, the pizzas are similar to Me n Ed's, in terms of the way it's cooked, and it's quite delicious!

Because there are a good number of people there during lunch, they tend to have 2-3 pizzas ready (most of the time) and then there is the salad bar and breadsticks.

Recently, it was my first experience in which they kept running out of pizza as many people were there and had mostly salad and breadsticks, waiting for more pizza to come out.  But by the time I got in line, the pizza was gone.  But that was a rare occasion.

Also, the price did go up for buffet lunch from $9.25 to $10, which is still very good.

But I really do enjoy eating at V.I.P. Pizza. and the staff are very courteous.

A cool pizzeria and definitely worth visiting if you are hungry for pizza.

data.title: A very cool family-driven pizza restaurant
data.text:
V.I.P. Pizza is a restaurant I frequently visit when I'm in the Tulare area.  The owners have been very cool and customer service has been solid.

It does get crowded during lunch time and sometimes, the pizza is gone.  But the owners have been good in making sure pizza is replaced.

Good amount of games for children, two projectors for people to watch sports games.

But for the most part, it's a pizza buffet that you get your money's worth.  As for the pizza, it reminds me of Me & Eds but much cheaper in price.

data.title: Surprised at how great their pizza was
data.text: We could not decide what to eat, so thought pizza would be the best bet, and thinking of finding a chain joint we at least would know what they are like (we have had some pretty bad pizza in the past), but VIP had a very high rating on reviews, so we said, let's try...and boy, my husband is Mr. Picky, he loved his, saying the crust had an excellent taste and he is not a crust man either, mostly he enjoys the toppings, so that tells me a lot.  He has a 1/2 and 1/2 pepperoni/olive and Canadian bacon/pineapple, he raved over it even told the manager.  I had a very thin crust, extra crispy cheese, and it was just how I ordered, and not greasy fake cheese either, and they claim to use only real ingredients.  I also had a salad from their salad bar, great choices of items, kept filled items.  Highly recommend trying this place.

data.title: Great pizza and fun atmosphere
data.text:
I popped in for the lunch pizza buffet. I was told when I ordered there would be a short wait since they make the pizza fresh for the buffet, unlike some other pizza buffets I had visited in the past. I was invited to enjoy a salad from the all-you-can eat salad bar. The vegetables were fresh, the salad bar was neat and clean, and my salad was very good.

When the pizza arrived at the buffet it was hot, fresh and delicious. The dough is light, but the crust is crisp. The topping were generous and it was wonderful.

I would come back again for lunch or for a casual night with family and friends to have a beer and some great pizza.

data.title: Always great food and friendly service
data.text: Want great food at a good price with "feel like family" service? Then go to V.I.P.! The pizza, bread sticks, and salad bar are the best in the valley if not anywhere.

data.title: EXCELLENT
data.text: This restaurant has a full menu for delivery. Their pizza is the best I have ever had. The pizza crust is crunchy on the bottom soft on the top. The toppings are plentiful. The sauce tastes wonderful (other pizza places I order no sauce because I am not a fan of tomato sauce) I crave this pizza. In fact I am going to order some right now. You should too.

data.title: Great Pizza, and they don't skimp on toppings!
data.text:
First, they deliver, so that was a real bonus at the end of a long day enjoying the N.P.  Next, no issue with a simply order selecting our three toppings.

Pricing was better than average, they took the CC over the phone and got the order correct w/o issues.

Delivery was pleasantly quick and the driver presented himself professionally.  The pizza was outstanding!  We ordered a simple pizza of pepperoni, green peppers and pineapple and they covered the entire pizza with pepperoni, then topped it with green peppers and pineapple after cooking.  This resulted in a wonderful pizza with fresh toppings that were not soggy or mush, but full of flavor over a pleasant crust that was thin, but not excessively so and not doughy either.  Great flavor, fully cooked and warm when delivered.

This was a real treat at the end of a long day when we did not feel like going out to find dinner.  Much better than average for delivery pizza and will be a place we certainly go back to when we are in Exeter or close by in the future.

data.title: travlngi13
data.text: pizza is okay,but don't go to the lunch buffet if you're in a hurry. They only put out 2 pizzas at a time,and you have to fight to get any. I sat for 10 minutes with no pizza made,so when they put 2 out it was a mad rush from the customers.

data.title: Awesome pizza
data.text: I really enjoy pizza and VIP is a great pizza.  Also they have an awesome lunch special.  All you can eat for about seven bucks.

data.title: Sports & Pizza <3
data.text: Definitely a great place for the whole family. My boyfriend always drags me there to watch sports but the PIZZA makes it worth it!

data.title: An unexpected find!
data.text:
Stopped in for lunch on the way back to Southern California.  A great very fresh salad bar and always freshly baked pizza for the lunch buffet.  Don't let the small containers of salad bar choices fool you, the containers are small to fit a large number of choices, and they are constantly replenished so everything is always available.  The pizza is always replenished as well, never sitting on the counter, always hot & fresh.  The price is a great bonus.

Why is an unexpected find?  Great food, great price in a little town off the 99 Highway, a very nice surprise.  So next time you are traveling either to or from Northern California or Southern California, stop in for lunch or dinner to get you home.

data.title: Great lunch time gettaway
data.text: Stopped in to VIP for lunch near the end of our trip. We were all very suprised that the $6 lunch buffet was so good. Very nice little salad bar and the pizza was extremely good. Very crunchy crust and different variety. The staff were very nice and treated you like you were from the town.

data.title: The BEST pizza in Tulare
data.text: This restaurant will treat you like family. And on top of that this pizza is good quality unlike all those other pizza chains with their cardboard food.  Good location in the downtown area. Whenever I visit here I just have to stop by.  Try it out you won't regret it.
